--- body ---
## Context

/celebrate sweep after PR #51 (CI workflow) found 7 hook scripts missing
`set -euo pipefail`. Silent failures in hook scripts are dangerous: a broken
guard (e.g., `guard-commit-on-main.sh`) may exit 0 despite an error,
silently allowing what it was meant to block.

Affected files:
- scripts/guard-destructive-bash.sh
- scripts/block-pr-merge-in-worktree.sh
- scripts/shell-init.sh
- scripts/guard-commit-on-main.sh
- scripts/lint-on-edit.sh
- scripts/warn-stale-rules.sh
- scripts/on-start.sh

## Actions

1. Add `set -euo pipefail` as the second line (after the shebang) in each
   script. Review each for commands that legitimately may fail (grep, test)
   and add `|| true` where needed.
2. Add a CI check to `CI.yml` (requires 0015, now merged): grep all
   `scripts/*.sh` for `set -euo pipefail`; fail if any are missing.
   This becomes the standing regression guard.

## Test

Remove `set -euo pipefail` from one script; expect CI red.

## Exit criteria

- All `scripts/*.sh` have `set -euo pipefail`.
- CI job enforces it.
- No hook regression (manual smoke: trigger each hook scenario once).
